      "title": "Citizen Lab: Law Enforcement Used Webloc to Track 500 Million Devices via Ad Data",
      "url": "https://thehackernews.com/2026/04/citizen-lab-law-enforcement-used-webloc.html",
      "published": "2026-04-11T06:02:00+00:00",
      "summary": "Hungarian domestic intelligence, the national police in El Salvador, and several U.S. law&nbsp;enforcement and police departments have been attributed to the use of an advertising-based global geolocation surveillance system called&nbsp;Webloc.\nThe tool was developed by Israeli company Cobwebs Technologies and is now sold by its successor Penlink after&nbsp;the two firms merged in July&nbsp;2023"
